FBIS4-27494 "dreas106_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 30 May 1994 North Korea 27, 28 May U.S. `Air War Exercise' Noted 27, 28 May U.S. `Air War Exercise' Noted SK3005055194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0516 GMT 30 May 94 SK3005055194 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists staged an air war exercise, deploying scores of overseas-based nuclear-capable F-16 and F-15 fighter-bombers, assault planes, pursuit-assault planes, VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] assault planes and anti-submarine planes in South Korea on May 27 and 28, military sources said. This provocative war exercise was aimed at examining the quick deployment of overseas-based warplanes of various types in the Korean peninsula and their capacity of entering into action. This war gamble was part of their preparations for a war of aggression to stifle the DPRK by force of arms.
